data.title: Our Donors
data.meta_description: Thank you for supporting Missouri Western through your gifts to the Foundation this past year. Private support is more important than ever, and we appreciate the individuals, businesses and organizations that donated in fiscal year 2023. Every attempt has been made to include all of our contributors below. If your name is omitted from the
data.text:
The Western League for Excellence is an honorary giving society for donors who give undesignated gifts of $100 or more to the Missouri Western Annual Fund. It is at the cornerstone of Missouri Western’s fund-raising efforts.

The League was established by the MWSU Foundation for the purpose of demonstrating appreciation to alumni and friends of the University who give undesignated gifts, as well as to promote the concept of such giving.

The financial resources received from these donors help provide funds for the Foundation’s projects in support of the work of the University. In addition, League members may demonstrate their interest in other ways. They stay informed about the progress at the University, promote the University among friends and potential students and, when possible, attend University events. A strong Western League for Excellence gives visibility to members’ support of the University, which often helps potential donors, faculty members, and students to have confidence in Missouri Western.
